WEBVTT

00:01.268 --> 00:03.068
You moving back in
with Renn?

00:03.070 --> 00:04.136
Nope.

00:04.138 --> 00:05.938
She's moving down to San Antonio
with her grandma.

00:05.940 --> 00:08.273
Come with us.
Wanna be with us, right?

00:08.275 --> 00:10.943
Julia: Baz, you know what it
means to accept shit from her.

00:10.945 --> 00:12.545
Baz: This way, we don't
have to sneak around.

00:12.547 --> 00:14.947
You can
come over whenever.

00:14.949 --> 00:16.615
Baz: I have some apartments
on the other strand.

00:16.617 --> 00:18.351
I want you
to move in to one.

00:18.353 --> 00:19.952
You're giving me
an apartment?

00:19.954 --> 00:21.220
I'm giving you
an out.

00:21.222 --> 00:23.155
The thing with Baz --
sorry, okay?

00:23.157 --> 00:24.823
It's weird for you
'cause you're my brother,

00:24.825 --> 00:26.825
but it's not
actually weird.

00:26.827 --> 00:28.627
It's, like, normal.

00:28.629 --> 00:30.763
Looks good.

00:30.765 --> 00:33.699
Hey,
load it in.

00:33.701 --> 00:35.500
Smurf:
Everything went well?

00:35.502 --> 00:36.902
Julia:
Piece of cake.

00:36.904 --> 00:38.704
Deran: Pope would do anything
for us.

00:38.706 --> 00:40.639
We can't just
leave him inside, man.

00:40.641 --> 00:42.107
We gotta do something.

00:42.109 --> 00:43.709
We need to break him
the hell out of there,

00:43.711 --> 00:44.977
is what
we need to do.

00:44.979 --> 00:46.511
It's like
every other job.

00:46.513 --> 00:48.914
We just have to find a weakness
and we plan it out.

00:48.916 --> 00:51.984
Well,
let's do it.
Okay.

00:51.986 --> 00:53.753
♪♪

00:56.191 --> 00:59.925
♪♪

00:59.927 --> 01:05.798
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:05.800 --> 01:09.802
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:09.804 --> 01:12.905
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:15.743 --> 01:21.080
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:21.082 --> 01:24.884
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:24.886 --> 01:28.187
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:31.893 --> 01:34.760
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:34.762 --> 01:38.564
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:38.566 --> 01:42.435
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:42.437 --> 01:46.105
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:46.107 --> 01:50.375
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:50.377 --> 01:54.246
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:54.248 --> 01:58.250
♪ Got a ♪

01:58.252 --> 02:00.319
Baz: Pope.

02:00.321 --> 02:01.520
[ Knock on door ]

02:01.522 --> 02:04.190
Pope.
Pope, come on.

02:05.526 --> 02:07.660
Pope!
Come on, man!

02:07.662 --> 02:09.795
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

02:09.797 --> 02:12.131
[ Chuckles ]
You're okay. You're okay.

02:12.133 --> 02:13.866
You forget
to set your alarm?

02:13.868 --> 02:16.068
[ Claps hands ]
Gotta get on the road.

02:16.070 --> 02:17.870
Let's go.
Come on.

02:17.872 --> 02:20.072
I gotta take a shower.
No, no, no.

02:20.074 --> 02:21.807
Just brush your teeth
and put on some deodorant.

02:21.809 --> 02:23.142
I'm taking a shower,
man.

02:23.144 --> 02:24.543
Man.

02:24.545 --> 02:26.545
Look, uh,
it'll be two minutes.

02:26.547 --> 02:27.813
We'll still
beat traffic.

02:27.815 --> 02:29.715
Please. Go.

02:31.018 --> 02:34.253
[ Water running ]

02:37.558 --> 02:40.493
Come on, man.

02:40.495 --> 02:42.828
What's up?

02:42.830 --> 02:44.297
Nothing's up!
We're late!

02:44.299 --> 02:45.831
Let's go!

02:45.833 --> 02:47.632
You nervous
or something?

02:47.634 --> 02:49.702
What do I got
to be nervous about?

02:49.704 --> 02:52.705
Well, Smurf doesn't like
when we do banks.

02:52.707 --> 02:55.508
[ Chuckles ]

02:55.510 --> 02:58.177
Just hurry up,
alright?

02:58.179 --> 03:01.981
♪♪

03:01.983 --> 03:03.849
So, what's the most
I can send?

03:03.851 --> 03:05.851
$2,500.
Per day.

03:05.853 --> 03:07.520
Per day?
Okay.

03:07.522 --> 03:17.530
♪♪

03:17.532 --> 03:21.334
♪♪

03:21.336 --> 03:23.402
ID?

03:23.404 --> 03:28.073
♪♪

03:28.075 --> 03:30.075
Thanks,
Mr. Cartwright.

03:30.077 --> 03:32.745
Julian, huh?
I grew up in Ramona.

03:32.747 --> 03:35.681
Oh, yeah?
Right on.

03:35.683 --> 03:38.150
Should be available
in two business days.

03:38.152 --> 03:40.019
Oh, wait.
Maybe three.

03:40.021 --> 03:42.755
I mean, Singapore's on the other
side of the world, so...

03:42.757 --> 03:44.890
You can trace it
on the app.

03:44.892 --> 03:46.825
Alright.

03:46.827 --> 03:48.694
♪♪

03:48.696 --> 03:50.896
Thanks.

03:50.898 --> 03:56.369
♪♪

03:56.371 --> 03:57.570
Morning, baby.

03:57.572 --> 03:59.171
Where'd you go
so early?

03:59.173 --> 04:01.306
That's for
three spools.

04:01.308 --> 04:02.708
They'll have three more
next week.

04:02.710 --> 04:05.911
Just three?

04:05.913 --> 04:08.581
Thought Reggie could get us
more than that.

04:08.583 --> 04:10.983
That's all they had
for us.

04:11.919 --> 04:17.456
♪♪

04:17.458 --> 04:19.592
Hey, baby?

04:19.594 --> 04:21.060
♪♪

04:21.062 --> 04:23.196
I got you something.

04:23.198 --> 04:32.605
♪♪

04:32.607 --> 04:35.074
Oh.
A kimono.

04:35.076 --> 04:37.209
You don't like it?

04:37.211 --> 04:39.544
It's just not
really my style.

04:39.546 --> 04:42.415
Well, your style seems to be
ripped, plaid,

04:42.417 --> 04:44.083
and previously owned,

04:44.085 --> 04:46.218
so I'll take that
as a compliment.

04:46.220 --> 04:48.287
No, no.
I mean, it's cool.

04:48.289 --> 04:50.222
It's just
for around the house.

04:50.224 --> 04:53.692
You know,
it's a little reward

04:53.694 --> 04:57.296
for handling this job
so well.

04:57.298 --> 05:06.772
♪♪

05:06.774 --> 05:09.708
♪♪

05:09.710 --> 05:12.377
[ Sighs ]

05:12.379 --> 05:17.250
♪♪

05:17.252 --> 05:19.251
Penny: What?

05:19.253 --> 05:22.054
Why do you have to get up
so early?

05:22.056 --> 05:25.424
Because some of us actually
have to work regular hours.

05:29.530 --> 05:32.465
I could, uh,
call a mover,

05:32.467 --> 05:35.934
get your stuff over here,
if you wanted.

05:35.936 --> 05:37.336
It's Noah's stuff,
too,

05:37.338 --> 05:40.907
and, uh,
he's not returning my calls.

05:42.076 --> 05:44.877
Did you
tell him about us?

05:44.879 --> 05:47.079
Penny: I did.

05:47.081 --> 05:50.082
And?

05:50.084 --> 05:51.851
He's hurt.

05:57.292 --> 06:00.025
Well, we can get you some stuff
from IKEA for now,

06:00.027 --> 06:01.294
if you don't want
to deal with him.

06:01.296 --> 06:03.362
Just let me know
how much it costs.

06:03.364 --> 06:05.698
What are we
doing here, J?

06:05.700 --> 06:07.967
What do you mean?

06:07.969 --> 06:10.102
An apartment
by the beach?

06:10.104 --> 06:11.704
I can't afford this
on my own,

06:11.706 --> 06:13.706
and I know your family
owns the building,

06:13.708 --> 06:15.240
but it doesn't
feel right.

06:15.242 --> 06:16.641
It's not
a big deal.

06:16.643 --> 06:18.110
It is for me.

06:19.780 --> 06:20.980
We can...

06:20.982 --> 06:23.950
go pick out furniture
together.

06:26.321 --> 06:30.589
I've, um -- I've got a lot
of shit going on right now.

06:30.591 --> 06:33.326
♪♪

06:33.328 --> 06:36.395
So, I should just
stay here,

06:36.397 --> 06:40.065
alone,
waiting for you to call?

06:40.067 --> 06:43.402
Look,
I like you, okay?

06:43.404 --> 06:46.605
I'm in a position
to help you out, and I want to.

06:46.607 --> 06:49.474
♪♪

06:49.476 --> 06:51.744
So, can you just
be okay with that for now?

06:51.746 --> 06:53.546
You know?

06:53.548 --> 06:55.748
♪♪

06:55.750 --> 06:58.283
Sure.

06:58.285 --> 07:03.556
But just so you know,
you are my situation.

07:03.558 --> 07:13.566
♪♪

07:13.568 --> 07:20.239
♪♪

07:20.241 --> 07:22.307
Well, well, well.

07:22.309 --> 07:27.246
If it isn't my favorite
known offspring.

07:27.248 --> 07:30.049
What's up?
[ Groans ]

07:30.051 --> 07:31.850
You're late.

07:31.852 --> 07:33.252
Oh, relax, dude.

07:33.254 --> 07:35.654
It's Saturday.

07:35.656 --> 07:37.390
It's Friday.

07:37.392 --> 07:38.657
It's Friday?

07:38.659 --> 07:40.459
Yeah.
Okay.

07:40.461 --> 07:42.661
Whatever.
You win, alright?

07:42.663 --> 07:43.863
[ Inhales sharply ]

07:43.865 --> 07:45.264
How you been?

07:45.266 --> 07:47.199
What happened
to your face?

07:47.201 --> 07:49.735
Oh. My girlfriend.
[ Chuckles ]

07:49.737 --> 07:52.271
'Cause she thought I made a move
on her sister,

07:52.273 --> 07:55.340
which technically,
I did not.

07:55.342 --> 07:56.609
Did you order?

07:56.611 --> 07:58.744
Hello.
Can I get you
some coffee?

07:58.746 --> 08:02.214
Yes, please, and, uh,
tell me about your pancakes.

08:02.216 --> 08:04.417
The best.
Billy:
Oh. Okay.

08:04.419 --> 08:06.419
Waitress: Great.
Give me the biggest
stack you got,

08:06.421 --> 08:09.554
and I'll have, uh,
three eggs scrambled

08:09.556 --> 08:10.823
with cheddar cheese
on top...

08:10.825 --> 08:12.024
Okay.

08:12.026 --> 08:14.627
...uh, bacon crispy,
uh, toast,

08:14.629 --> 08:16.228
uh, sourdough,
if you got it, please.

08:16.230 --> 08:18.431
Mm-hmm.
And for you?

08:18.433 --> 08:20.099
I'm good with just coffee.
Thank you.

08:20.101 --> 08:21.967
You're not eating?
No.

08:21.969 --> 08:24.369
Alright, well, you're buying,
'cause you invited me.

08:24.371 --> 08:25.838
This is my kid.

08:25.840 --> 08:27.973
I can see it.

08:27.975 --> 08:30.575
♪♪

08:30.577 --> 08:32.711
Oh, boy.

08:32.713 --> 08:36.048
Bad habit right there.

08:36.050 --> 08:40.119
So,
how's things, man?

08:40.121 --> 08:41.386
I've been great,
man.

08:41.388 --> 08:44.257
I, uh,
been dope-free for...

08:44.259 --> 08:46.859
11 months now,
I think.

08:46.861 --> 08:48.527
I mean,
I still smoke weed,

08:48.529 --> 08:51.664
but they call it,
uh, California sober.

08:51.666 --> 08:53.466
[ Chuckles ]

08:53.468 --> 08:56.669
These are
for my face.

08:56.671 --> 08:58.403
[ Bell dings ]

08:58.405 --> 09:00.539
You look tired.

09:00.541 --> 09:03.876
Yeah, I haven't really
been sleeping too much.

09:03.878 --> 09:06.812
Why?
What's up?

09:06.814 --> 09:09.348
[ Dishes clinking ]

09:09.350 --> 09:11.216
Alright, I know you didn't
call me down here

09:11.218 --> 09:12.818
because you missed me,
alright?

09:12.820 --> 09:14.219
Nope.

09:14.221 --> 09:16.889
[ Sighs ]

09:16.891 --> 09:19.558
I, uh...
[ Clears throat ]

09:19.560 --> 09:22.595
I need -- I need you to, uh,
help me out with something.

09:23.631 --> 09:26.231
[ Chuckles ]

09:26.233 --> 09:27.566
Boy, never thought
I'd hear those words

09:27.568 --> 09:29.768
coming out
of your mouth, ever.

09:29.770 --> 09:32.771
Okay. Cool.
Alright.

09:32.773 --> 09:34.373
What's the job?

09:34.375 --> 09:37.643
It's not a job.

09:37.645 --> 09:39.444
You, uh --

09:39.446 --> 09:42.581
You spent time in lockdown
in San Diego, right?

09:42.583 --> 09:44.249
Yeah. Twice.

09:44.251 --> 09:46.451
Ain't the worst, but it's not
anyplace I want to get back to.

09:46.453 --> 09:49.054
Why?
Do you
know anybody inside?

09:49.056 --> 09:51.991
You know, any guards, staff,
anybody like that?

09:51.993 --> 09:55.127
Yeah, I mean, I probably still
know a couple guys in there.

09:55.129 --> 09:57.062
Okay.

09:57.064 --> 09:58.397
I need
some information.

09:58.399 --> 10:00.199
I just need,
you know,

10:00.201 --> 10:02.267
blueprints,
files, records,

10:02.269 --> 10:04.637
anything I can
get my hands on, really.

10:05.740 --> 10:09.208
Yeah, I could probably help
with something like that.

10:09.210 --> 10:10.409
Okay.

10:10.411 --> 10:12.144
Five grand.

10:12.146 --> 10:14.079
Alright,
fair enough.

10:14.081 --> 10:16.148
There's not a lot to steal
in county lockup, though.

10:16.150 --> 10:18.684
Do -- Do you know
anybody inside or not?

10:18.686 --> 10:21.620
Yeah. I think I know somebody
I can talk to.

10:21.622 --> 10:23.756
Okay. Great.

10:23.758 --> 10:25.824
♪♪

10:25.826 --> 10:27.960
Enjoy your pancakes.
Really?

10:27.962 --> 10:30.696
Yeah,
you know where to find me.

10:30.698 --> 10:32.131
♪♪

10:41.442 --> 10:43.776
What're those?

10:43.778 --> 10:46.045
Letters from colleges.

10:46.047 --> 10:47.980
They want me
to apply.

10:47.982 --> 10:51.484
The testing company
sent them my SAT scores.

10:52.587 --> 10:55.721
Are you
gonna do it?

10:55.723 --> 10:57.390
I don't know.

10:57.392 --> 11:00.525
Can't hurt, though,
right?

11:00.527 --> 11:03.195
Must be nice
being smart.

11:03.197 --> 11:05.330
Shut up.
You<i> are</i> smart.

11:05.332 --> 11:07.332
[ Papers rustling ]

11:07.334 --> 11:10.736
Smart enough to know
not to steal from Smurf.

11:10.738 --> 11:12.405
Smurf's gonna lecture me
about stealing?

11:12.407 --> 11:14.473
That should be good.

11:14.475 --> 11:16.075
It's different
and you know it.

11:16.077 --> 11:17.710
Well,
I'm not worried.

11:19.680 --> 11:23.482
♪♪

11:23.484 --> 11:26.085
Is that what you need
the money for?

11:26.087 --> 11:28.287
College?

11:28.289 --> 11:30.756
I need it
to get out of here.

11:30.758 --> 11:32.291
Maybe college,
maybe something else,

11:32.293 --> 11:34.359
but either way,
I'm out.

11:34.361 --> 11:39.098
♪♪

11:39.100 --> 11:41.033
What about you?

11:41.035 --> 11:42.635
What about me?

11:42.637 --> 11:44.369
What, you gonna
stay here forever

11:44.371 --> 11:47.440
and let Smurf
keep running your life?

11:47.442 --> 11:49.909
'Cause you know
she will.

11:49.911 --> 11:53.245
♪♪

11:53.247 --> 11:56.381
Are you two looking to hold out
for a certain number,

11:56.383 --> 11:58.050
or are you more interested
in a quick sale?

11:58.052 --> 12:00.519
No. Quick sale.
Soon as possible.

12:00.521 --> 12:02.054
It's all paid off.
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

12:02.056 --> 12:04.389
It's been in the family
for a while now.

12:04.391 --> 12:06.258
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
Motivated sellers.

12:06.260 --> 12:08.994
Love it.

12:08.996 --> 12:11.997
So, how much do you think
we can get for it?

12:11.999 --> 12:13.732
Well, look,
it's a small place.

12:13.734 --> 12:17.336
Uh, I'll have to check comps,
get the inspection,

12:17.338 --> 12:18.804
but with the proximity
to the ocean,

12:18.806 --> 12:20.405
the strand,
the view,

12:20.407 --> 12:23.276
I'm thinking
just north of a million.

12:23.278 --> 12:24.477
No more?

12:24.479 --> 12:25.811
Well, the reality is
in this market,

12:25.813 --> 12:27.212
a quick buy is gonna go
to a seller

12:27.214 --> 12:30.283
who is gonna knock it down
and put up some condos.

12:30.285 --> 12:31.950
Condos?

12:31.952 --> 12:34.487
You indicated that you were
interested in a quick sale.

12:34.489 --> 12:36.021
We are.

12:36.023 --> 12:38.357
I've been working with
a Newport Beach developer.

12:38.359 --> 12:40.959
Nice guy, all cash deals,
and moves quick.

12:40.961 --> 12:43.028
I think
he'll love this place.

12:43.030 --> 12:44.563
Okay,
sounds good.
Great.

12:44.565 --> 12:46.966
So, we'll schedule
an inspection,

12:46.968 --> 12:50.169
engage a title company,
do death disclosure.

12:50.171 --> 12:51.971
Wait, what?

12:51.973 --> 12:54.573
Uh, California requires you
to disclose

12:54.575 --> 12:55.975
any deaths
on the property.

12:55.977 --> 12:57.710
Has anyone died here?

12:57.712 --> 13:00.313
It's usually not a problem
unless it's something violent,

13:00.315 --> 13:02.381
but buyers
can be particular.

13:02.383 --> 13:04.984
But I thought you just said they
were gonna get it torn down.

13:04.986 --> 13:06.451
Mm,
I don't make the rules.

13:06.453 --> 13:08.521
I just
make the sales.

13:08.523 --> 13:11.924
So,
no deaths, right?

13:11.926 --> 13:13.960
No.

13:15.062 --> 13:21.800
♪♪

13:21.802 --> 13:23.402
[ Clears throat ]

13:23.404 --> 13:25.871
Man,
this car reeks.

13:25.873 --> 13:27.940
There's gotta be a way to tell
if a car smells like shit

13:27.942 --> 13:29.342
before you steal it.

13:29.344 --> 13:31.677
[ Chuckles ]

13:31.679 --> 13:33.812
Okay. You see that?
It's quarter to one.

13:33.814 --> 13:35.614
These people are still doing
business on their lunch breaks.

13:35.616 --> 13:37.616
Five minutes,
it's gonna clear out.

13:37.618 --> 13:39.818
Maybe six cars,
four of them employees.

13:39.820 --> 13:42.087
Is that
when he takes his lunch?
Yeah.

13:42.089 --> 13:44.156
They probably give him
a half hour. He always takes 45.

13:44.158 --> 13:47.426
He gets in his car
and he drives off somewhere.

13:47.428 --> 13:49.161
Maybe home for lunch,
maybe somewhere else.

13:49.163 --> 13:51.564
I don't care.
Either way, he's gone.

13:51.566 --> 13:56.101
Maybe he's got a girlfriend
he goes and sees.

13:56.103 --> 13:58.371
Yeah, maybe.

13:58.373 --> 14:02.107
♪♪

14:02.109 --> 14:04.377
Look, we gotta
talk about something, okay?

14:04.379 --> 14:05.644
♪♪

14:05.646 --> 14:07.046
[ Sighs ]

14:07.048 --> 14:10.649
Did you leave flowers
in Cath's car again?

14:10.651 --> 14:12.251
♪♪

14:12.253 --> 14:13.452
Huh?

14:13.454 --> 14:16.521
You heard me.

14:16.523 --> 14:18.257
Yeah.

14:18.259 --> 14:20.860
So?
Why?

14:20.862 --> 14:22.527
It's a nice thing to do
for somebody.

14:22.529 --> 14:24.663
Yeah, for me, because,
you know, she's my girlfriend.

14:24.665 --> 14:26.198
I got a kid with her.
When you do it, it's weird.

14:26.200 --> 14:28.401
When was the last time
you gave her flowers?

14:28.403 --> 14:30.335
Jesus Christ,
man.

14:30.337 --> 14:31.604
We talked about this.

14:31.606 --> 14:32.872
I don't like it.
Okay?

14:32.874 --> 14:34.673
Okay.
Cath doesn't like it,
either.

14:34.675 --> 14:36.008
It makes her
feel uncomfortable.

14:36.010 --> 14:37.210
Did she
tell you that?

14:37.212 --> 14:39.344
No, she doesn't
have to tell me that.

14:39.346 --> 14:41.080
Don't do it again.

14:41.082 --> 14:43.015
Is that a problem?
No,
it's not a problem.

14:43.017 --> 14:44.750
Good.

14:44.752 --> 14:46.886
♪♪

14:46.888 --> 14:48.754
[ Sighs ]

