climb up over here

19:08.750 --> 19:11.617
and peer
off the edge,

19:11.619 --> 19:14.420
trying to
psych himself up.

19:14.422 --> 19:17.889
So, anyway, one day,
I followed him up,

19:17.891 --> 19:19.759
and I waited
until he turned his back,

19:19.761 --> 19:21.293
and then I just...

19:21.295 --> 19:24.964
tackled him off the roof
into the water.

19:24.966 --> 19:26.899
And we barely cleared
the concrete, man.

19:26.901 --> 19:28.634
He was screaming,

19:28.636 --> 19:30.169
and then
you had Smurf over here,

19:30.171 --> 19:32.638
who was just
laughing her ass off.

19:32.640 --> 19:35.307
[ Chuckles ]

19:35.309 --> 19:36.776
Yeah, man, we, uh --

19:36.778 --> 19:39.779
yeah,
we had some good times here.

19:39.781 --> 19:47.653
♪♪

19:47.655 --> 19:49.755
Morning.

19:51.793 --> 19:53.993
That cereal's like
two years old.

19:53.995 --> 19:56.328
Yeah,
tell me about it.

19:56.330 --> 19:58.530
One thing
about Smurf's --

19:58.532 --> 20:00.666
cereal was
always crunchy.

20:00.668 --> 20:04.336
What are you doing here
so early?

20:04.338 --> 20:06.071
Your contact
come through yet?

20:06.073 --> 20:08.740
Yeah.
Getting everything you wanted.

20:08.742 --> 20:10.409
Okay. Good.

20:10.411 --> 20:12.544
Hey, listen, I've been thinking
about this place.

20:12.546 --> 20:16.548
It's a lot of
untapped potential, you know?

20:16.550 --> 20:18.951
For instance,
this thing.

20:18.953 --> 20:20.820
Did that
come with the joint?

20:20.822 --> 20:22.822
Is that
why it's here?
Yeah. So?

20:22.824 --> 20:24.490
So, it's, you know,
a shitty version

20:24.492 --> 20:26.358
of a game old people play
on cruise ships.

20:26.360 --> 20:28.160
What? What are you talking
about? People love that thing.

20:28.162 --> 20:29.228
People play that shit
all the time.

20:29.230 --> 20:30.630
Yeah, well,
if there was a pool table,

20:30.632 --> 20:31.831
people would play it
all the time

20:31.833 --> 20:33.032
and drink
as they were playing.

20:33.034 --> 20:34.433
Plus, you could have
two pool tables.

20:34.435 --> 20:37.169
This thing's huge.
It's taking up all the space.

20:37.171 --> 20:39.771
And let's get a couple
of sexy bartenders, you know?

20:39.773 --> 20:41.040
Ah, geez.

20:41.042 --> 20:42.642
With some skin,
some cleavage, you know?

20:42.644 --> 20:44.376
Okay.
I got some shit I gotta do,

20:44.378 --> 20:47.379
but you can stay here
if you want.

20:47.381 --> 20:49.181
I just wasn't planning
on opening up the bar

20:49.183 --> 20:50.449
until later,
is all.

20:50.451 --> 20:52.918
Let me open it.
No.

20:52.920 --> 20:54.119
Come on, man.
I'm here anyways.

20:54.121 --> 20:56.255
If there's anywhere
[Clears throat]

20:56.257 --> 20:59.725
I know my way around,
it's a bar, right?

20:59.727 --> 21:01.126
Come on.
Alright.

21:01.128 --> 21:03.262
Fine.

21:03.264 --> 21:04.463
Thank you.

21:04.465 --> 21:05.931
[ Keys jingle ]

21:05.933 --> 21:11.937
Um, hey, tell me --
what did your, um,

21:11.939 --> 21:16.141
emotionally and mentally stable
eldest brother do

21:16.143 --> 21:18.077
to get put back
in the joint?

21:20.882 --> 21:23.749
He murdered somebody.

21:23.751 --> 21:25.150
What?
Yeah, he, uh -- he --

21:25.152 --> 21:28.754
he killed
Baz's girlfriend.

21:28.756 --> 21:30.489
Shit.

21:30.491 --> 21:33.025
Wow.

21:33.027 --> 21:35.427
I guess it was bound to happen,
right?

21:35.429 --> 21:40.900
I mean, Pope's face
is probably the last thing

21:40.902 --> 21:42.902
more than a few
unlucky people saw.

21:42.904 --> 21:45.037
It's not like that.

21:45.039 --> 21:46.638
Pope and Baz
were tight.

21:46.640 --> 21:48.774
Pope cared about Baz.

21:48.776 --> 21:51.443
He cared about Cath.

21:51.445 --> 21:54.179
Look...

21:54.181 --> 21:57.583
Listen, Pope has
a lot of issues.

21:57.585 --> 22:00.252
[ Clears throat ]
And love ain't one of them.

22:00.254 --> 22:03.188
♪♪

22:03.190 --> 22:05.925
[ Sighs ] So, what are you gonna
do about the money?

22:05.927 --> 22:08.060
Just piss it all away
on Pope?

22:08.062 --> 22:09.995
Oh, you'd like to know that,
wouldn't you?

22:09.997 --> 22:13.865
I-I am genuinely concerned
about you.

22:13.867 --> 22:15.467
That's what
I'm concerned about, okay?

22:15.469 --> 22:19.138
Not the money.
We're selling everything.

22:19.140 --> 22:22.074
And splitting it evenly.

22:22.076 --> 22:25.745
J's taking care of it all
right now, so...

22:25.747 --> 22:27.213
J?
Listen to yourself.

22:27.215 --> 22:30.416
J stepped up
when he didn't have to.

22:30.418 --> 22:31.951
[ Sighs ]
