this one time, okay?

22:56.644 --> 22:58.844
Wake up.

22:58.846 --> 23:01.313
♪♪

23:01.315 --> 23:03.515
Leave Pope in jail
where he belongs.

23:03.517 --> 23:06.718
Give Craig his share
if you feel like you have to.

23:06.720 --> 23:08.053
That's fine.

23:08.055 --> 23:12.458
But do not give a God damn dime
to J, okay?

23:12.460 --> 23:13.926
The kid
doesn't deserve it.

23:13.928 --> 23:15.995
He doesn't
deserve shit.

23:15.997 --> 23:19.531
♪♪

23:19.533 --> 23:23.302
Come on.

23:25.006 --> 23:27.139
Here.

23:28.476 --> 23:29.875
[ Knock on door ]

23:29.877 --> 23:32.612
Baz!

23:33.615 --> 23:36.215
It's a waste of time.
Can we just go?

23:36.217 --> 23:38.017
Shut up.
Come on.

23:38.019 --> 23:40.486
I said come on!

23:40.488 --> 23:42.989
Baz!

23:53.835 --> 23:57.903
[ Door closes ]

23:57.905 --> 24:01.274
[ Moaning ]

24:13.655 --> 24:17.056
♪♪

24:17.058 --> 24:18.991
Julia,
where's the bathroom?

24:18.993 --> 24:20.792
What the hell?

24:20.794 --> 24:22.728
♪♪

24:22.730 --> 24:26.465
Hey, why -- why didn't you
tell me you were coming over?

24:26.467 --> 24:28.067
♪♪

24:28.069 --> 24:30.402
Julia: Let's go.
Come on.

24:30.404 --> 24:31.937
♪♪

24:31.939 --> 24:33.339
Jesus, Julia.

24:33.341 --> 24:35.207
Look,
I met her on the beach.

24:35.209 --> 24:37.677
We came in
to have a beer.
Bye.

24:37.679 --> 24:39.078
[ Scoffs ]

24:39.080 --> 24:41.747
Oh, come on.
Grow up, Julia.

24:41.749 --> 24:45.551
We never had some
exclusive thing here.

24:45.553 --> 24:47.819
God damn it!

24:47.821 --> 24:50.022
♪♪

24:50.024 --> 24:52.558
That's the last
free shot --
What are you gonna do?
Hit me?

24:52.560 --> 24:53.893
Go on!

24:53.895 --> 24:55.361
Hit me!

24:55.363 --> 24:57.829
Like father,
like son, right?

24:57.831 --> 25:00.099
♪♪

25:00.101 --> 25:02.301
Deran, Craig,
let's go.

25:02.303 --> 25:04.836
Now!

25:04.838 --> 25:09.108
♪♪

25:09.110 --> 25:10.576
Two minutes.

25:10.578 --> 25:13.079
[ Gun cocks ]

25:18.520 --> 25:20.252
What's the matter?

25:20.254 --> 25:23.122
I'm not a weirdo.

25:23.124 --> 25:25.391
What, man?
I-I'm not a weirdo.

25:25.393 --> 25:27.126
You said
I was being a weirdo,

25:27.128 --> 25:29.661
leaving flowers for Cath,
and I am not a weirdo.

25:29.663 --> 25:31.997
Jesus, you want to do this
right now, man?

25:31.999 --> 25:33.999
Okay.

25:34.001 --> 25:35.667
Cath is mine.

25:35.669 --> 25:37.403
She's the mother of my kid,
you understand?

25:37.405 --> 25:39.138
What I do
or what I don't do with her

25:39.140 --> 25:40.339
is none of your
God damn business.

25:40.341 --> 25:41.741
She deserves better
and so does Lena,

25:41.743 --> 25:43.475
and you would see that
if you weren't so busy

25:43.477 --> 25:46.478
trying to put your dick
in anything that'll hold still!

25:46.480 --> 25:47.679
♪♪

25:47.681 --> 25:49.148
What did you
just say to me?

25:49.150 --> 25:52.484
You want me to say it again?
She deserves better.

25:52.486 --> 25:55.287
You had your chance with her,
and she chose me.

25:55.289 --> 25:56.688
What does that
tell you?

25:56.690 --> 25:58.824
You scare her.
Yeah. You do.

25:58.826 --> 26:01.693
You scare a lot of people,
but you know what?

26:01.695 --> 26:04.964
You don't scare me.
Mnh-mnh.

26:04.966 --> 26:06.432
♪♪

26:06.434 --> 26:09.034
We're gonna talk
about this later.

26:09.036 --> 26:10.903
You ready?
I'm always ready.

26:10.905 --> 26:12.104
[ Gun cocks ]

26:12.106 --> 26:19.579
♪♪

26:24.385 --> 26:27.520
[ Alarm blaring ]

26:31.525 --> 26:32.724
[ Engine starts ]

26:32.726 --> 26:36.062
[ Tires squeal ]

26:40.602 --> 26:43.202
Come on, come on, come on.

26:45.072 --> 26:47.607
Come on, Pope.

26:47.609 --> 26:49.541
Come on.

26:49.543 --> 26:50.943
[ Siren wails ]

26:50.945 --> 26:53.412
God damn it.

26:55.617 --> 26:58.618
God damn it.

26:58.620 --> 26:59.952
God damn it.

26:59.954 --> 27:02.754
Come on, Pope.

27:02.756 --> 27:04.556
♪♪

27:04.558 --> 27:07.026
Stay back!

27:07.028 --> 27:10.362
[ Siren wails, tires squeal ]

27:10.364 --> 27:12.965
Shit.

27:12.967 --> 27:14.700
♪♪

27:14.702 --> 27:17.969
[ Horn honks ]

27:17.971 --> 27:20.439
[ Siren wails ]

27:20.441 --> 27:29.982
♪♪

27:29.984 --> 27:39.124
♪♪

27:39.126 --> 27:40.726
[ Siren wails ]

27:40.728 --> 27:44.129
[ Tires screech ]

27:44.131 --> 27:48.267
[ Siren wails ]

27:48.269 --> 27:56.542
♪♪

27:56.544 --> 28:00.812
[ Horn honks ]

28:00.814 --> 28:05.751
♪♪

28:05.753 --> 28:09.889
[ Siren wails ]

28:09.891 --> 28:19.899
♪♪

28:19.901 --> 28:27.639
♪♪

28:27.641 --> 28:33.579
[ Siren wails ]

28:33.581 --> 28:35.847
[ Dog barks ]

28:35.849 --> 28:42.054
♪♪

28:42.056 --> 28:46.125
[ Siren wails ]

28:46.127 --> 28:50.596
[ Tires screech ]

28:50.598 --> 28:53.799
Stay right there!
Don't move!

28:53.801 --> 28:58.203
♪♪

28:58.205 --> 29:02.208
Get down on your knees!

29:02.210 --> 29:03.675
Cross your ankles!

29:03.677 --> 29:08.680
♪♪

29:08.682 --> 29:11.751
Don't move.

29:11.753 --> 29:14.086
[ Handcuffs click ]

29:14.088 --> 29:21.227
♪♪

29:22.764 --> 29:24.764
Get inside.

29:24.766 --> 29:26.098
Now.

29:26.100 --> 29:28.700
Hey, hey, hey.

29:28.702 --> 29:31.170
What's going on?

29:31.172 --> 29:32.905
What happened?

29:32.907 --> 29:34.774
Baz.

29:34.776 --> 29:36.776
What about Baz?

29:36.778 --> 29:38.844
[ Sighs ]

29:38.846 --> 29:40.712
I took Deran and Craig
to check out his new place,

29:40.714 --> 29:43.916
and he was there
with some girl.

29:43.918 --> 29:45.785
Oh.

29:45.787 --> 29:48.187
Yeah.

29:48.189 --> 29:50.189
Who was it?
[ Sighs ]

29:50.191 --> 29:51.590
Some slut
he met off the beach,

29:51.592 --> 29:55.060
probably on vacation
from Arizona.

29:55.062 --> 29:56.528
God,
he's such a piece of shit.

29:56.530 --> 29:58.097
I never
want to see him again.

30:04.071 --> 30:06.005
Don't act all bummed.

30:06.007 --> 30:09.275
You never wanted me and Baz
together in the first place.

30:11.212 --> 30:14.213
Baz is Baz.

30:14.215 --> 30:16.215
He always
looks out for himself,

30:16.217 --> 30:18.451
and you
should've known that.

30:20.754 --> 30:23.322
Thanks. That makes me feel
so much better.

30:26.227 --> 30:29.561
You're a good person,
Julia.

30:29.563 --> 30:31.230
You deserve
someone who's --

30:31.232 --> 30:34.233
who's gonna be nice
to you,

30:34.235 --> 30:38.437
buy you stuff,
bring you flowers.

30:38.439 --> 30:42.107
♪♪

30:42.109 --> 30:44.109
That's not Baz.

30:44.111 --> 30:45.978
♪♪

30:45.980 --> 30:48.113
You're awesome.

30:48.115 --> 30:51.450
♪♪

30:51.452 --> 30:53.585
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you.

30:53.587 --> 30:56.055
Pope,
don't be a weirdo.

30:56.057 --> 30:57.990
Andrew!

30:57.992 --> 31:00.192
I'm --
I'm sorry, Julia.

31:00.194 --> 31:01.527
Please --
Please don't be mad at me.

31:01.529 --> 31:03.595
Don't be --
Andrew, what the hell?

31:03.597 --> 31:05.665
You're my brother.
Please. Please.

31:05.667 --> 31:09.468
I know you don't think there's
something wrong with me, but...

31:09.470 --> 31:11.803
♪♪

31:11.805 --> 31:13.138
...but there is.

31:13.140 --> 31:14.806
♪♪

31:14.808 --> 31:16.475
Please.

31:16.477 --> 31:18.810
Please.

31:18.812 --> 31:20.880
Please.

31:20.882 --> 31:22.081
Please.

31:22.083 --> 31:24.483
♪♪

31:24.485 --> 31:25.685
J: Billy?

31:25.687 --> 31:28.020
We're counting on Billy
to get us something?

31:28.022 --> 31:29.621
Yeah.

31:29.623 --> 31:31.623
He's got a contact
at the jail.

31:31.625 --> 31:34.026
Could probably get us
any info we want.

31:34.028 --> 31:35.294
You talk to Pope?

31:35.296 --> 31:37.363
No,
he's still in lockdown.

31:37.365 --> 31:39.498
Gotta get him on board,
man.

31:39.500 --> 31:41.567
Pope will get on board
when the time comes.

31:41.569 --> 31:43.035
Yeah.

31:43.037 --> 31:46.038
Can Billy's guy get us details
on prisoner transport?

31:46.040 --> 31:48.040
Yeah, probably.

31:48.042 --> 31:49.841
[ Lighter clicks ]

31:49.843 --> 31:53.178
[ Lighter clatters ]

31:53.180 --> 31:54.846
What about the money?

31:54.848 --> 31:56.248
Yeah, no shit.

31:56.250 --> 31:59.318
How much we getting
after we sell all this stuff?

31:59.320 --> 32:01.053
Well,
Baz's place is listed.

32:01.055 --> 32:04.189
Um, Deran's gonna close
in a week.

32:04.191 --> 32:07.859
We got the bar, the gym,
the bowling alley.

32:07.861 --> 32:09.929
If we liquidate
all of the money and --

32:09.931 --> 32:12.197
Alright,
so how much?

32:12.199 --> 32:14.333
$5.4 million total,

32:14.335 --> 32:17.203
so, between four of us,
that's $1.3 million.

32:17.205 --> 32:18.870
Each.

32:18.872 --> 32:21.873
Damn.

32:21.875 --> 32:23.743
How do we access it?

32:23.745 --> 32:26.746
We use the passports Craig
got us to set up bank accounts.

32:26.748 --> 32:28.814
Give me the details,
I'll send you the money

32:28.816 --> 32:31.016
on the day
that we break out Pope.

32:31.018 --> 32:34.019
You're gonna need to set up new
accounts for wherever you go,

32:34.021 --> 32:37.557
but we can't transfer any money
before the day of.

32:37.559 --> 32:40.359
It would attract attention
otherwise.

32:40.361 --> 32:42.962
And what about Pope?

32:42.964 --> 32:45.765
♪♪

32:45.767 --> 32:47.833
Pope will come
with me.

32:47.835 --> 32:49.635
♪♪

32:49.637 --> 32:51.103
Just until
he gets on his feet,

32:51.105 --> 32:54.373
figures out
where he wants to go.

32:54.375 --> 32:57.709
You can put his share
into my account.

32:57.711 --> 33:01.247
Yeah,
that's cool with me.

33:01.249 --> 33:04.250
So, um, that's it.

33:04.252 --> 33:07.253
♪♪

33:07.255 --> 33:09.655
We snatch Pope,
and then we run.

33:09.657 --> 33:12.924
♪♪

33:12.926 --> 33:16.262
What?

33:16.264 --> 33:18.930
It's a lot of work
you've done.

33:18.932 --> 33:21.400
♪♪

33:21.402 --> 33:23.535
Selling all
of Smurf's properties

33:23.537 --> 33:26.071
and setting up the businesses,
you know?

33:26.073 --> 33:28.874
You've been playing
the long game, haven't you?

33:28.876 --> 33:31.811
♪♪

33:31.813 --> 33:34.079
Sure you just want
to cut and run?

33:34.081 --> 33:37.149
♪♪

33:37.151 --> 33:39.285
It's for Pope,
right?

33:39.287 --> 33:41.086
♪♪

33:41.088 --> 33:43.155
It's like you said.

33:43.157 --> 33:45.224
He would do
the same for us.

33:45.226 --> 33:51.030
♪♪

33:51.032 --> 33:53.965
Yeah.

33:53.967 --> 33:56.101
It's for Pope.

33:56.103 --> 34:02.608
♪♪

34:15.423 --> 34:17.924
Oh, shit.

34:21.495 --> 34:23.596
Are you
making dinner?

34:25.366 --> 34:26.832
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

34:26.834 --> 34:28.734
Here.

34:30.504 --> 34:33.772
Looks good on you.

34:33.774 --> 34:37.476
Thanks.
It's very comfortable.

34:39.848 --> 34:44.182
You know, I have
a great marinara recipe.

34:44.184 --> 34:47.185
You don't have to use
that store-bought shit.

34:47.187 --> 34:48.587
[ Liquid pours ]

34:48.589 --> 34:51.624
It's easier this way.

34:52.861 --> 34:55.527
You and the boys
have fun today?

34:55.529 --> 34:56.995
[ Bottle thuds ]

34:56.997 --> 34:59.098
Mm-hmm.

35:00.534 --> 35:03.803
Craig told me
that Baz was with a girl.

35:08.809 --> 35:12.078
Go ahead.
Say it.

35:12.080 --> 35:15.013
Say what?

35:15.015 --> 35:16.983
"I told you so."

35:19.888 --> 35:22.821
You know,
some lessons...

35:22.823 --> 35:26.692
you just have to learn
the hard way.

35:26.694 --> 35:28.761
What's the lesson here?

35:30.564 --> 35:33.833
You can always count on men
to be men.

35:34.902 --> 35:36.034
♪♪

35:36.036 --> 35:39.905
Believe it or not,
that can be very useful.

35:39.907 --> 35:42.040
♪♪

35:42.042 --> 35:45.111
Come here.

35:45.113 --> 35:48.714
♪♪

35:48.716 --> 35:51.583
Are you gonna listen
to your mom now?

35:51.585 --> 35:59.458
♪♪

35:59.460 --> 36:00.526
Billy:
Oh, the boss is here.

36:00.528 --> 36:01.994
Everybody look busy.

36:01.996 --> 36:04.463
Can I talk to you
in the back for a sec?

36:04.465 --> 36:06.132
Yeah.

36:06.134 --> 36:08.467
Got his serious face.

36:08.469 --> 36:11.069
I'll be back.

36:11.071 --> 36:12.604
What's up?

36:12.606 --> 36:15.474
Can you
shut the door?

36:15.476 --> 36:17.609
Yeah.

36:17.611 --> 36:20.078
[ Clears throat ]

36:20.080 --> 36:21.880
What's going on?

36:21.882 --> 36:24.883
[<i> Rock music playing</i>
<i> in distance</i> ]

36:24.885 --> 36:28.487
There's 5 grand.

36:28.489 --> 36:30.556
Nice.
For what?

36:30.558 --> 36:32.891
For the contact.

36:32.893 --> 36:35.027
I'll, uh,
take it from here.

36:35.029 --> 36:37.295
No. Uh, I'm not giving you
the contact.

36:37.297 --> 36:39.966
That's...
Billy,
I'm not asking.

36:39.968 --> 36:43.502
Wait, you think you can just
buy me off?

36:43.504 --> 36:46.639
Is that what you think?
You can't.

36:46.641 --> 36:48.507
[<i> Music continues</i> ]

36:48.509 --> 36:51.644
You'd be
making a mistake.

36:51.646 --> 36:54.513
Yeah, it wouldn't be
the first one.

36:54.515 --> 36:57.049
There you go.
10 grand...

36:57.051 --> 36:58.651
for the contact.

36:58.653 --> 37:00.987
[ Sighs ]

37:00.989 --> 37:02.655
You don't have to do this,
alright?

37:02.657 --> 37:06.525
You don't have to do
this whole Pope thing.

37:06.527 --> 37:08.326
No, no. Listen to me.
Listen to me.

37:08.328 --> 37:10.929
You could come up north with me,
alright?

37:10.931 --> 37:12.331
I got this guy
in Carmel.

37:12.333 --> 37:14.667
He's, like, an ex, um,
you know, ad exec

37:14.669 --> 37:16.068
for some big firm
in San Francisco,

37:16.070 --> 37:19.205
and I talked my way i-into
his Fourth of July party, right?

37:19.207 --> 37:21.473
I scoped the place out, okay?
He's one of these ex-hippies.

37:21.475 --> 37:24.943
He thinks, like, the world runs
on love and flowers, right?

37:24.945 --> 37:26.679
He's got
no real security.

37:26.681 --> 37:28.814
His wife has
a jewelry collection.

37:28.816 --> 37:30.416
Looks like, you know,
like it came from

37:30.418 --> 37:32.018
Liz Taylor's house.
Billy.

37:32.020 --> 37:33.952
♪♪

37:33.954 --> 37:36.355
Just give me the contact,
please.

37:36.357 --> 37:37.690
♪♪

37:37.692 --> 37:41.127
[ Sighs ]

37:42.763 --> 37:46.032
Alright.
If that's what you want.

37:46.034 --> 37:49.768
♪♪

37:49.770 --> 37:53.239
[ Cellphone chimes ]

37:53.241 --> 37:54.707
Thanks.
[ Sighs ]

37:54.709 --> 37:57.243
You at least gonna tell me
what you're doing,

37:57.245 --> 37:59.045
where you're gonna go?

37:59.047 --> 38:01.447
I don't know.
Probably Indonesia.

38:01.449 --> 38:02.715
Oh, Jesus.

38:02.717 --> 38:04.316
What? What?
[ Sighs ]

38:04.318 --> 38:06.919
There's a north list
of non-extradition countries,

38:06.921 --> 38:08.987
and I'm not going
to Libya.

38:08.989 --> 38:12.725
Besides, I already know
someone down in Indonesia.

38:12.727 --> 38:15.193
Probably don't want to see me,
but...

38:15.195 --> 38:18.997
♪♪

38:18.999 --> 38:21.834
Smurf really did a number
on you boys.

38:23.271 --> 38:26.405
Well,
it's your life.

38:26.407 --> 38:30.476
You want to piss it away
saving the psychopath,

38:30.478 --> 38:32.278
go right ahead.

38:32.280 --> 38:36.749
♪♪

38:36.751 --> 38:38.751
Well...

38:38.753 --> 38:41.620
♪♪

38:41.622 --> 38:43.556
...I'll see you around.

38:43.558 --> 38:47.293
♪♪

38:47.295 --> 38:49.361
Yeah.

38:49.363 --> 38:52.098
♪♪

38:52.100 --> 38:54.633
[ Door opens ]
You know, Billy...

38:54.635 --> 38:59.772
♪♪

38:59.774 --> 39:02.575
Don't worry about it.

39:02.577 --> 39:12.585
♪♪

39:12.587 --> 39:14.787
♪♪

39:14.789 --> 39:17.123
You almost drowned
in that pool.

39:17.125 --> 39:18.657
♪♪

39:18.659 --> 39:21.327
You mean
you almost drowned me.

39:21.329 --> 39:23.129
No,
that was Deran.

39:23.131 --> 39:24.797
Both of you.

39:24.799 --> 39:28.801
[ Sighs ] Yeah.

39:28.803 --> 39:31.470
Well,
no hard feelings, man.

39:31.472 --> 39:33.806
But you did have it coming,
though.

39:33.808 --> 39:35.141
We're cool.

39:35.143 --> 39:38.210
[ Chuckles ]

39:38.212 --> 39:41.180
$1.3 million.

39:43.151 --> 39:46.953
Got a lot
of shit right, J.

39:46.955 --> 39:49.822
Smurf always said
you were smart.

39:49.824 --> 39:51.890
Like Julia.

39:51.892 --> 39:54.493
♪♪

39:54.495 --> 39:57.296
I never had anything
against her, you know.

39:57.298 --> 40:00.299
Your mom.

40:00.301 --> 40:02.501
I know.

40:02.503 --> 40:05.171
I was only little
when she left.

40:05.173 --> 40:08.507
I only saw her one,
maybe two times after that.

40:08.509 --> 40:09.908
♪♪

40:09.910 --> 40:14.112
But you --
you never liked me much.

40:14.114 --> 40:17.850
You never really liked me much,
either.

40:17.852 --> 40:20.987
Yo, you show up,
Smurf brings you in,

40:20.989 --> 40:22.721
all of a sudden,
everybody's listening to you.

40:22.723 --> 40:24.991
I mean,
what's to like?

40:24.993 --> 40:26.324
Smurf used me.

40:26.326 --> 40:28.394
Well,
she used everyone.

40:28.396 --> 40:29.862
♪♪

40:29.864 --> 40:33.399
It was never about anyone else
other than her, man.

40:33.401 --> 40:36.869
♪♪

40:36.871 --> 40:40.406
I was wrong about you,
though.

40:40.408 --> 40:43.209
You set us up good.

40:43.211 --> 40:44.877
Now you're helping
with the Pope shit.

40:44.879 --> 40:47.746
That's --
That's something.

40:47.748 --> 40:49.882
♪♪

40:49.884 --> 40:53.419
It's real.

40:53.421 --> 40:55.421
Family, right?

40:55.423 --> 40:58.224
Yeah.

40:58.226 --> 41:00.492
Family.

41:00.494 --> 41:06.365
♪♪

41:06.367 --> 41:09.501
Man: Pope.

41:09.503 --> 41:11.770
Pope.

41:11.772 --> 41:14.240
Pope, come on.

41:14.242 --> 41:16.309
[ Sighs ]

41:35.663 --> 41:38.531
[ Sighs ]

41:38.533 --> 41:40.533
♪♪

41:40.535 --> 41:43.669
[ Laughs ]

41:43.671 --> 41:48.074
♪♪

41:48.076 --> 41:50.609
What are you
doing here?

41:50.611 --> 41:51.877
Me?

41:51.879 --> 41:53.612
I should be asking you
that question.

41:53.614 --> 41:56.482
You're the one who said you were
never coming back to prison.

41:56.484 --> 41:58.484
♪♪

41:58.486 --> 42:02.288
They found Cath.

42:02.290 --> 42:06.024
In the desert,
where I put her.

42:06.026 --> 42:07.225
♪♪

42:07.227 --> 42:09.295
I told them
the truth.

42:09.297 --> 42:12.098
I told them
what I did.

42:12.100 --> 42:13.632
Like I said,
it wasn't your fault.

42:13.634 --> 42:15.768
Bullshit.

42:15.770 --> 42:17.970
I did it.

42:17.972 --> 42:20.439
Nothing ch--
changes that.

42:20.441 --> 42:23.842
♪♪

42:23.844 --> 42:26.044
I deserve this.
Oh, yeah?

42:26.046 --> 42:28.847
Says who?

42:28.849 --> 42:30.849
Huh?

42:30.851 --> 42:32.985
Says who?

42:32.987 --> 42:39.858
♪♪

42:39.860 --> 42:41.994
I loved her,
man.

42:41.996 --> 42:45.331
I-I really did.

42:45.333 --> 42:46.999
I know.

42:47.001 --> 42:48.801
What you did --

42:48.803 --> 42:51.537
it wasn't you,
okay?

42:51.539 --> 42:54.006
It was Smurf.

42:54.008 --> 42:56.875
It's always Smurf.

42:56.877 --> 42:58.076
She killed Cath.

42:58.078 --> 42:59.745
She killed me.
She killed Julia.

42:59.747 --> 43:02.481
With Julia,
it just took longer.

43:02.483 --> 43:04.016
Hey.

43:04.018 --> 43:05.217
Pope.

43:05.219 --> 43:07.886
She made you
what you are.

43:07.888 --> 43:09.688
She knew
what she was doing.

43:09.690 --> 43:13.091
Smurf got what was coming
to her, but you --

43:13.093 --> 43:15.561
you never
had a chance, did you?

43:15.563 --> 43:17.563
I didn't have
a chance.

43:17.565 --> 43:20.366
No.

43:20.368 --> 43:29.708
♪♪

43:29.710 --> 43:30.909
♪♪

43:30.911 --> 43:33.045
Why are you here?

43:33.047 --> 43:34.847
I don't know.

43:34.849 --> 43:37.716
It's probably all those meds
they're giving you.

43:37.718 --> 43:41.920
[ Laughs ]

43:41.922 --> 43:45.057
Yeah.

43:45.059 --> 43:47.926
I left you that day.

43:47.928 --> 43:51.397
At the bank.

43:51.399 --> 43:54.933
You made sure I got out first,
and then...

43:54.935 --> 43:57.003
I left you.

43:57.005 --> 43:58.937
♪♪

43:58.939 --> 44:01.407
No.

44:01.409 --> 44:05.077
No, you tripped
on a wastebasket,

44:05.079 --> 44:06.478
I pinned
the guard down.

44:06.480 --> 44:07.880
You --
You had to go.

44:07.882 --> 44:10.148
It was a couple of seconds,
but you had to get out,

44:10.150 --> 44:12.084
otherwise,
we were both gonna get caught.

44:12.086 --> 44:14.620
What's the point of that?
Y-Y-You had to.

44:14.622 --> 44:18.424
Did I?
You had no choice.

44:18.426 --> 44:21.493
You took all that shit
for all of us.

44:21.495 --> 44:24.096
All of it.

44:24.098 --> 44:26.098
You paid.

44:26.100 --> 44:28.367
♪♪

44:28.369 --> 44:31.103
You don't belong here,
Pope.

44:31.105 --> 44:33.372
You understand?

44:33.374 --> 44:36.108
You don't belong here.

44:36.110 --> 44:39.111
♪♪

44:39.113 --> 44:41.714
[ Sighs ]
Damn it.

44:41.716 --> 44:44.250
This is not real.
Stupid, stupid.

44:44.252 --> 44:45.718
Stop.
Stop it.

44:45.720 --> 44:47.319
This shit again.
I'm not gonna do this again.

44:47.321 --> 44:48.987
You're not real!
God, man.

44:48.989 --> 44:50.589
What?
You paid.

44:50.591 --> 44:52.258
Stop it!
...three, four, five...

44:52.260 --> 44:55.327
You don't belong here.
No real.
He's not real!

44:55.329 --> 44:56.795
You don't belong here.

44:56.797 --> 44:58.197
[ Groans ]

45:01.335 --> 45:03.936
[ Sighs ]

45:06.874 --> 45:10.208
[ Sighing ]

45:10.210 --> 45:17.683
♪♪

45:17.685 --> 45:20.018
Hey!

45:20.020 --> 45:24.022
♪♪

45:24.024 --> 45:25.491
Phone call.

45:25.493 --> 45:35.401
♪♪

45:36.104 --> 45:46.112
Phone call.

45:46.114 --> 45:56.122
♪♪

45:56.124 --> 46:02.762
♪♪
